ation 9 — 2026-04-22T10:05:51Z — OK\n197\t- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n198\t\n199\t## Iteration 10 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n200\t- **Item**: [routes] Convert `backend/src/routes/public-profile.ts` to envelope responses; update profile test coverage.\n201\t- **Changes**:\n202\t  - Rewrote `GET /{identifier}` in `backend/src/routes/public-profile.ts`:\n203\t    - Success → `ok(c, { userId, username, avatarUrl, heatMultiplier, stats, createdAt })`.\n204\t    - Missing profile → `err(c, 404, API_ERROR_CODES.NOT_FOUND, \"Profile not found\")`.\n205\t    - Lookup failure → `err(c, 500, API_ERROR_CODES.PRECONDITION_FAILED, \"Failed to fetch profile\")`.\n206\t    - Response schemas use `envelope(PublicPlayerProfileSchema)` for 200 and `ErrorEnvelopeSchema` for 404/500.\n207\t    - Removed imports of `errorMessage` (from `api-errors.ts`) and `ErrorResponseSchema` (from `validators.ts`) — legacy helpers still live there for the cleanup iteration.\n208\t    - Renamed `catch (err)` binding to `catch (lookupError)` to avoid shadowing the imported `err` helper.\n209\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/profile.test.ts`:\n210\t    - `GET /public-profile/:username` success test: destructures `body.data` from envelope (`body.ok === true`).\n211\t    - `GET /public-profile/:user_id` success test: asserts envelope shape, accesses fields via `body.data.userId` / `body.data.username`.\n212\t    - `GET /public-profile/:identifier` 404 test: now asserts `body.ok === false` and `body.error.code === \"NOT_FOUND\"` (was `body.error === \"NOT_FOUND\"`).\n213\t    - The \"no wallet field\" test is text-based and continues to pass unchanged.\n214\t- **Verification**:\n215\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n216\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n217\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/profile.test.ts` → 13/13 passed\n218\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/waitlist-contract.test.ts` → 41/41 passed\n219\t  - Full unit suit